As far as aggro reducing spells. I really don't see a need for it. They need to make mages more dominate from the pet side of things. Mages are suppose to be limited in terms of dd because our pets are SUPPOSE to make up for the difference. With alot of the AoE that exist in PoP Pets are near useless. The Wizard pet needs to become a WIZARD PET. This pet should be the pet that we go to when the standard melee pet can not be used. It should be the added boost in dd we need when a standard melee pet can not be used. 
<br />

<br />
IMO a great change to the fire pet would be.....................
<br />

<br />
Does not have the ability to do melee damage.
<br />
Resistant to AoE dots/dd spells except dispell. 
<br />
Remove Root from the ability table
<br />
lvl 44-49 wizard spells for the 63 pet.....
<br />
Give player caster type mana pool
<br />
Make is so that it benefits from Clarity type buffs and a med command to keep it from casting when it is low on mana.
<br />
Also a /pet report mana would be nice
<br />
Make the pet unable to taunt 
<br />

<br />
Making these changes would really give mages that are in highend PoP encounters added damage while not making it so good that it replace the rogue type pets. I know my guild is still in the ToV stage. I would LOVE a pet like that. Once that i could break out on dragons like Sontalak, and Lendi/Eashen.  Melee pets are worthless for the most part vs. dispell mobs. They could really make the fire pet a limited big boost damage pet for a given encounter. Alot of times pets are not good to use because they push like mad. 
<br />

<br />
Also the lvl 65 pet needs work. IMO some changes that should be made.............
<br />

<br />
Add 1000hps
<br />
Add a extra 75-100dd to the root
<br />
Allow it to tripple attack
<br />
increase the max hit to 91-95.
<br />
*will never happen* change the root to a short duration snare.
<br />

<br />
Just some ideas  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /> 
