				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Since some of you obviously don't know what the deal is with the 65 Necro pet I'll elaborate. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
He's broken. It's not like Rathes Son where we decided the Lure Based root wasn't good enough and that he wasn't that much of an upgrade and couldn't stun or tank.
<br />

<br />
He's a Shadow Knight without spells or a pet.
<br />

<br />
They originally intended for the level 65 Necro pet to be a Shadownight, with the spell lineup of a Shadowknight. (I'm guessing he should have Harm Touch, Banshee Aura, Vampiric Embrace and the SK Aggro increasing buff.)
<br />

<br />
I've charmed SK mobs and when they aren't in combat, they cast these buffs on themselves.
<br />

<br />
Apparently the SK's of the world got pissed off and started screaming that a pet was going to be taking their class defining abilities (Dunno why the Monks, Rogues and Wizards never whined about pets being modeled after them but that's another story.)
<br />

<br />
Verant decided to appease the SK's by removing all Shadowknight abilities from the pet JUST before PoP went live.
<br />

<br />
So now we have a Warrior pet with Shadowknight damage output, Shadowknight damage mitigation and ZERO spells.
<br />

<br />
In other words he's a sissie.
<br />

<br />
(Not that Rathe's son doesn't need some dev lovin.. but the Necro pet is first in line so pbthththth) <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=375146" target="_blank" class="postlink">Gojirax</a> - 65 Arch Lich
