			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Who asked for some type of mage concussion? Someone please rationalize this for me, as it makes no sense whatsoever and is a waste of time.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
By looking at your magelo link it's painfully obvious that you aren't in a high end raiding guild.  Concussion is for those of us in the elemental planes fighting stuff that hits for 2700, not the mages romping around in PoV / PoN.  We both technically play the same game, but in no way shape or form do the same things.  Mages in the end game have a problem.
<br />

<br />
I had a guild member go to Fan Faire and ask the devs specifically for concussion for mages.  They won't lower our class aggro modifier - that would make it too easy and increase complaints on the graffe boards.  What's the fix?  Concussion.
<br />

<br />
Mages are the only high damage dealing focused class in the game with no way to lower or erase aggro.  This is a fact.
<br />

<br />
Rogues:  Evade + Escape
<br />
Monks: Feign Death
<br />
Wizards: Concussion
<br />
Ranger: Jolt
<br />
Mages: Nothing
<br />

<br />
In our DPS threads who are we comparing ourselves to every single time?  These classes above us.  All of them have a way to lower aggro except us.
<br />

<br />
So, what do mages have to do to currently try to keep pace in the end game?  Play the range game.  Get a Ceramic Sword of War with Extended Range 4, stick it in your range slot, and run way outside of the raid and nuke at maximum distance to keep aggro as low as possible even with SCS3.  There's a price to pay for doing this, however.  I'll make a water pet and even give him the summoned items of uselessness.  When I go running out to keep my DPS up, I lose any bard AE resists which means the pet now has my resists which are all in the 280-340 range with the usual buffs instead of straight 500s.
<br />

<br />
The pet gets gibbed in under 60 seconds.
<br />

<br />
So, now the thing that was supposed to make me close to a wizard and be my class strength just gave the boss mob 6 percent of an AA point and I'm now SOL.
<br />

<br />
But wait, the ranged aggro nerf coming means it's pointless for me to run out to lower aggro so I might as well just stay close to the bards next to the melee and suck the 30 percent loss in DPS because I don't have any way to survive other than nuking less.  We need to be able to lower aggro as a high damage class to maintain class legitimacy.  God knows the wizard to mage ratio in most end game non zerg guilds is horrible right now.  12 wizards and 3 mages is a very typical ratio to have in a server-best guild.  Giving us a concussion type spell at 65 where we need it is something those few of us still remaining in game living in the planes need.  Badly.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=35206">Master Diox</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of <a href="http://www.recon-eci.org">Reconstructed</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
